cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about unsupervised machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method that combines cross-lingual embeddings and n-gram language models, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and optimization. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of backtranslation, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (CV) and neural networks (NE). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.NE are also possible sub-categories.
